  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Sevoflurane has been used commonly in pediatric anesthesia since 1990. However, it has caused
      more emergency agitation (EA) that other inhalation agents and the incidence is up to 80%.
      Therefore, lower minimum alveolar concentration of sevoflurane will reduce the EA when it is
      used with remifentanil in pediatric general anesthesia.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
